{"type": "edit", "field": "description", "label": "Description", "before": "Schedule:\\n
 \u2014 Guests should plan to arrive between 4:00 PM and 5:00 PM.\\n
 \u2014 Upon arrival, participants are offered snacks, tea, and a communal prayer session, followed by dinner.\\n
 \u2014 Residents take turns showering in the evening.\\n
 \u2014 A breathalyzer test is administered upon entry each night to ensure sobriety.\\n\u2022 Phone Policy:\\n
 \u2014 Personal phones are collected and stored downstairs, where they are also charged overnight.\\n\u2022 Sleeping Arrangements:\\n
 \u2014 Each sleeping area accommodates up to 10 beds per room.\\n
 \u2014 Daily Routine:\\n\u2022 Wake-up is at 5:00 AM.\\n
 \u2014 Breakfast is served at 6:00 AM.\\n
 \u2014 All guests must leave the facility by 6:30 AM each morning.\\n\u2022 Program Duration:\\n
 \u2014 Guests may stay for up to 21 consecutive days.\\n
 \u2014 If a participant misses a night without calling ahead, they forfeit that night.\\n
 \u2014 If they miss two nights without communication, they lose their spot in the program.\\n
 \u2014 Guests are permitted to stay out for up to 2 nights during the 21-day period and can be re-admitted for one additional 21-day cycle if needed.\\n\u2022 Seasonal Availability:\\n
